.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
If set, the script looks for qrep-config.yaml under $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/qrep/ instead of ~/.config/qrep/.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to resolve ~/.config/qrep/qrep-config.yaml and ~/.qrep-config.yaml.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/qrep/qrep-config.yaml
System-wide configuration file (lowest priority).
.TP
.I ~/.config/qrep/qrep-config.yaml
Per-user configuration file (XDG default location).
.TP
.I ~/.qrep-config.yaml
Per-user configuration file (home directory fallback).
.TP
.I ..qrep-config.yaml
Project-local configuration file in the current directory (highest priority).
